                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">The handwriting changes from careful and neat at the very beginning (quire I) to mediocre (quires II-XII). It appears irregular throughout the Ms. due to variations in ruling (space between the lines differs: e.g., fol. 43r; slant writing lines: e.g., fols. 16rv, 17rv, 19rv, 36rv); broad, irregularly spaced and shaped letters (e.g., fols. 26ra, 34vab, 49vb); form of 'six' ፮, looking like "compressed" number 'seven'.<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic">
<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h4" script="Ethiopic">
The handwriting is similar to that of the scribe Zä-Wäldä Maryam (see e.g., QSM-001 [1745], QSM-007 [1745], MR-008 [1770-1775], UM-042 [1760-1800].<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
